President Biden and Prime Minister Trudeau met in the Oval Office to discuss various issues, including climate change, global health, and infrastructure needs. They emphasized the importance of working together to address these challenges and promote equitable economic recovery. The leaders also discussed the possibility of tax incentives for electric vehicles and the potential impact on the trade agreement between the US and Canada. President Biden stated that they would discuss the matter further as the legislation progresses. Additionally, President Biden mentioned that a diplomatic boycott of the Beijing Olympics is being considered. The meeting lasted until around 1:55 PM EST.